<div class="inky-pen">
	<aside class="bankruptcy-notice">
		<strong>Note:</strong> InkyPen filed for bankruptcy in December 2025. The business and its operations have ceased, and servers and publicly available software have been suspended. <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260301200127/https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/681220/view/516355643791114761?l=english" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Steam announcement (archived)</a>
	</aside>
	<p>
		<strong>InkyPen AS</strong>: Delivering digital U.S. comic books, manga and European comics internationally.<br />
		Sep. 2023 – Aug. 2025 (Company-wide layoffs due to economic conditions)<br />
		Full Stack Engineer, Bergen<br />
		<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20251121112954/https://inky-pen.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Home Page (archived)</a>, <a href="https://steamcommunity.com/app/681220" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Steam Community</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260301171529/https://store.steampowered.com/app/681220/InkyPen/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">(archived)</a>, <a href="https://www.nintendo.com/us/store/products/inkypen-switch/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Nintendo eShop</a>, <a href="https://kodansha.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B2B Customer Kodansha</a>
	</p>
	<p>
		Key contributor in a small, international team, responsible for developing and maintaining full-stack B2B and B2C digital distribution platforms. Collaborated closely with the Head Designer and Project Managers (B2B & B2C) to take features from concept to implementation in a fast-paced, agile environment. Experience with AWS cloud infrastructure, .NET backend, React/TypeScript frontend, and integration with external APIs.
	</p>
	<p>
		<strong>B2B solutions:</strong>
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Built physical checkout flow using Google Address Validation & Places Autocomplete APIs</li>
		<li>Built "On Sale" management system with support for large-scale CSV imports.</li>
		<li>Enhanced proprietary CMS with product reels, rich text editing, and improved submission workflows.</li>
		<li>Automated proprietary SSR cache-clearing workflows using AWS Step Functions, Lambda, S3, CloudFront, CDK, and the Cloudflare API.</li>
		<li>Overhauled internal dashboard listings using TanStack Table, introducing standardized backend filtering/search conventions.</li>
		<li>Automated digital metadata product import from an external XML-based database warehouse, supporting custom import rules and price mappings.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		<strong>B2C platform:</strong>
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Focused on C# ASP.NET backend powering a React web app (mobile-optimized) and a Unity-based Nintendo Switch client.</li>
		<li>Led development of an Electron wrapper client interfacing via IPC with Steam and Discord; managed Steam beta deployments.</li>
		<li>Reworked the Auth0 login system: Admin/staff account differentiation, integrated Steam authentication, enforced session limits, and improved account UX.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		<strong>Internal Admin Dashboard Enhancements:</strong>
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Built a support system using AWS SES to ingest user emails and web forms, enabling ticket creation, tagging, and internal management.</li>
		<li>Developed a mass scheduled email system with editable templates through the admin dashboard.</li>
		<li>Integrated AWS SES email event tracking (delivery, open, click) into internal tooling.</li>
		<li>Improved product, publisher management capabilities.</li>
		<li>Enhanced user content discovery and library UX.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		<strong>DevOps & Release:</strong>
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Owned full production deployments for both B2B and B2C.</li>
		<li>Managed complex release processes involving Amazon RDS, AWS CDK, CloudFormation, SAM, and EF Core migrations.</li>
	</ul>
</div>

